{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Quick Shadowing Drill: listen, repeat, and score timing + accuracy",
  "description": "Add a new Quick Practice card 'Shadowing Drill' that helps users improve fluency and prosody by repeating short native-paced sentences immediately after hearing them. This targets the listening+speaking core goal of the app.\n\nFlow:\n1. User opens the card from Home Quick Practice grid (similar to existing Quick Speak / Quick Conversation cards).\n2. Backend endpoint `POST /api/shadowing/sentence` returns a single short sentence (8ŌĆō18 words) appropriate for the user's level, plus expected speaking duration in seconds. Reuse `copilot_client` with a prompt in `app/prompts.py` (`SHADOWING_PROMPT`) that asks for: sentence, IPA-free phonetic hint, target_seconds, focus_tip (e.g., 'link \"want to\" ŌåÆ \"wanna\"'). Cache last 20 to avoid repeats per session.\n3. Frontend page `frontend/src/pages/Shadowing.tsx`:\n   - Plays the sentence via existing TTS (browser SpeechSynthesis, reuse helper from Pronunciation).\n   - Shows a 3-2-1 countdown, then records via Web Speech API (mirror pattern from `Pronunciation.tsx`).\n   - Computes two scores: (a) word-accuracy = % of expected words present in transcript (case/punct-insensitive), (b) timing-score = 100 - min(100, abs(actual_seconds - target_seconds)/target_seconds * 100).\n   - Displays combined score, the focus_tip, and 'Try again' / 'Next sentence' buttons. Shows transcript diff with missed words highlighted.\n4. Persist each attempt with `POST /api/shadowing/attempt` storing {sentence, transcript, accuracy, timing_score, duration_ms, created_at} in a new `shadowing_attempts` table for future trend display.\n5. Add route in `App.tsx` and a Quick Practice card on `Home.tsx` linking to `/shadowing`.\n\nSchema additions in `app/database.py` SCHEMA:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS shadowing_attempts (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  sentence TEXT NOT NULL,\n  transcript TEXT,\n  accuracy REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  timing_score REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  duration_ms INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n);\n```\nAnd append to `_MIGRATIONS` in `database.py` (idempotent, wrapped in try/except for already-exists):\n```python\n\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS shadowing_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, sentence TEXT NOT NULL, transcript TEXT, accuracy REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, timing_score REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, duration_ms INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')))\",\n```\n\nAdd a router `app/routers/shadowing.py` registered in `main.py`, a small DAL `app/dal/shadowing.py` with `save_attempt` and `recent_attempts`, and basic unit/integration tests covering: sentence generation returns expected fields, attempt save persists row, accuracy calculation handled in frontend (test via small util in `frontend/src/utils/shadowing.ts` with vitest). Keep UI consistent with existing Quick Practice card styling (dark mode + mobile responsive).",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/routers/shadowing.py", "app/database.py", "frontend/src/pages/Shadowing.tsx", "frontend/src/pages/Home.tsx", "frontend/src/App.tsx"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
