{
  "type": "bugfix",
  "title": "Strip emoji/decorative icons from SpeechSynthesis input in conversation",
  "description": "BUG-HIGH from backlog: SpeechSynthesis reads emoji aloud as literal names (e.g. '­¤śä' becomes 'smiling face'), disrupting listening practice. Fix:\n\n1. Create `frontend/src/utils/sanitizeForSpeech.ts` exporting `sanitizeForSpeech(text: string): string` that strips Unicode emoji ranges and decorative symbols before TTS. Use a regex covering: emoticons (U+1F600ŌĆōU+1F64F), misc symbols & pictographs (U+1F300ŌĆōU+1F5FF), transport (U+1F680ŌĆōU+1F6FF), supplemental symbols (U+1F900ŌĆōU+1F9FF), symbols & pictographs ext-A (U+1FA70ŌĆōU+1FAFF), dingbats (U+2700ŌĆōU+27BF), misc symbols (U+2600ŌĆōU+26FF), regional indicators (U+1F1E6ŌĆōU+1F1FF), variation selectors (U+FE0F), zero-width joiner (U+200D), and skin-tone modifiers (U+1F3FBŌĆōU+1F3FF). Also collapse the resulting extra whitespace and trim. Display text is unaffected (only the speak() argument).\n\n2. Modify `frontend/src/hooks/useSpeechSynthesis.ts`: in `speak()`, call `sanitizeForSpeech(text)` and pass the sanitized string into `new SpeechSynthesisUtterance(...)`. If the sanitized string is empty/whitespace, return early without speaking.\n\n3. Update conversation system prompts in `app/prompts.py` (the conversation-related system prompts used in `app/services/conversation_*` / Copilot calls) to append the instruction: 'Do not include emojis or decorative icons in your reply.' Add this line to each conversation/personality system prompt template so the model stops emitting emoji at the source.\n\n4. Add `frontend/src/utils/sanitizeForSpeech.test.ts` (Vitest) with cases: plain text passes through, single emoji removed ('Hello ­¤śä!' ŌåÆ 'Hello !'... then trimmed/collapsed to 'Hello!'), flag emoji (regional indicator pair) removed, ZWJ family sequence ('­¤æ©ŌĆŹ­¤æ®ŌĆŹ­¤æ¦') removed, skin-tone modifier ('­¤æŗ­¤ÅĮ') removed, variation selector heart ('ŌØż’ĖÅ') removed, all-emoji string returns empty.\n\nThis fixes a WCAG/UX regression where TTS pollutes the listening experience without affecting visual presentation.",
  "files_to_modify": [
    "frontend/src/utils/sanitizeForSpeech.ts",
    "frontend/src/utils/sanitizeForSpeech.test.ts",
    "frontend/src/hooks/useSpeechSynthesis.ts",
    "app/prompts.py"
  ],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "small"
}
