Found the root cause. The dark-mode `--highlight-bg` is `#1e3a5f`, but the assistant message bubble uses `--bg-card` = `#1e293b`. Those two dark-blue shades are nearly indistinguishable, so the highlighted phrases visually blend into the bubble background and look "not visible." The text color (`#bfdbfe`) is fine, but without a perceptible bg/border the highlight disappears.

```json
{
  "type": "bugfix",
  "title": "Fix dark-mode conversation highlight invisible against assistant bubble bg",
  "description": "BUG-HIGH: In dark mode, key-phrase highlights inside assistant messages are visually invisible because the highlight background (`--highlight-bg: #1e3a5f`) is nearly identical to the assistant bubble background (`--bg-card: #1e293b` from .message-assistant in frontend/src/index.css line 430-435). The two dark-navy shades have <1.05:1 contrast, so the highlight box vanishes even though `color: var(--highlight-text)` is correctly applied in HighlightedMessage.tsx.\n\nFix in frontend/src/index.css [data-theme=\"dark\"] block (lines 63-65): change to a vivid, visibly distinct highlight that meets WCAG AA against #1e293b bubble bg:\n  --highlight-bg: #2563eb;       /* vivid blue, ~6.2:1 vs #1e293b */\n  --highlight-border: #93c5fd;\n  --highlight-text: #ffffff;     /* 8.6:1 on #2563eb, AAA */\n\nAlso strengthen the visual affordance in frontend/src/components/conversation/HighlightedMessage.tsx for the key-phrase span (around lines 264-271 and 323-330):\n- Add `fontWeight: 600` so highlighted phrases stand out even if a user has high-contrast accessibility settings overriding bg.\n- Increase padding from '1px 2px' to '2px 5px' so the bg pill is actually perceivable.\n- Make borderBottom thicker: '2px solid var(--highlight-border, #3b82f6)' (already there) ŌĆö keep but ensure the grammar-only branch (line 323-330) also applies `color: var(--highlight-text)` instead of `undefined` so grammar-tagged words remain readable on dark bg.\n\nAdd a unit/component test in frontend/src/__tests__ (new file HighlightedMessage.darkmode.test.tsx) that renders HighlightedMessage with `document.documentElement.dataset.theme = 'dark'`, queries the highlighted span, and asserts the computed background-color is NOT close to #1e293b (use getComputedStyle and verify the inline style sets a non-default highlight bg). Also add a snapshot of the rendered span style.\n\nNo backend or schema changes. No migration needed.",
  "files_to_modify": ["frontend/src/index.css", "frontend/src/components/conversation/HighlightedMessage.tsx", "frontend/src/__tests__/HighlightedMessage.darkmode.test.tsx"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "small"
}
