```json
{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Lazy-load conversation reply helpers to cut /start and /message latency ~40%",
  "description": "Conversation /start and /message currently block on an extra LLM call to _extract_reply_helpers (suggestions, key_phrases, grammar_notes) AFTER the opening/AI reply is already known. Users wait for this extra call before seeing the AI message ŌĆö adding ~3-6s to the perceived 6-16s response time. Move helpers to a separate endpoint and have the frontend fetch them in the background while the user reads the AI reply.\n\nBackend changes (app/routers/conversation.py):\n1. Add a new endpoint `POST /api/conversation/helpers` taking `{conversation_id: int}`. It loads the latest assistant message for that conversation (via conv_dal.get_messages or a new helper), looks up the topic_label/difficulty from conv_dal.get_active_conversation (fall back to ended conversations too ŌĆö accept any status), then calls `_extract_reply_helpers` and returns `{phrase_suggestions, key_phrases, grammar_notes}`. Add a Pydantic request/response model. Use `safe_llm_call`-style error handling (returns empty arrays on failure, never 500).\n2. In `start_conversation`, REMOVE the `await helpers_coro` step in the non-role-swap path; return empty arrays for `phrase_suggestions`, `key_phrases`, `grammar_notes` so the response returns as soon as the opening is generated. Keep role_briefing (it's only generated in role_swap mode and is needed for the briefing UI). For the role_swap path, also stop awaiting helpers ŌĆö only await `_get_briefing()`.\n3. In `send_message`, REMOVE the trailing `await _extract_reply_helpers(...)` call after the parallel grammar+AI gather; return empty arrays for the three helper fields. The grammar feedback (errors/suggestions on the user's message) is unaffected ŌĆö only the helpers about the AI's reply are deferred.\n\nFrontend changes (frontend/src/api.ts and frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx ŌĆö file may be named ConversationPage.tsx; locate via the existing useConversation hook): \n4. Add `fetchConversationHelpers(conversationId)` API helper that POSTs to /api/conversation/helpers.\n5. In the conversation page, after the /start or /message response is rendered, fire `fetchConversationHelpers` in the background (no await blocking the UI). When it resolves, merge `phrase_suggestions`, `key_phrases`, `grammar_notes` into state so the UI updates. Show a subtle loading indicator (e.g., 'Loading suggestionsŌĆ”' or a spinner) in the suggestions/key-phrases panels while pending. If the call fails, silently leave arrays empty.\n\nTests (tests/integration/test_conversation_api.py):\n6. Add a test for POST /api/conversation/helpers happy path (mock copilot.ask_json to return suggestions/key_phrases/grammar_notes; assert response shape).\n7. Add a test that helpers endpoint 404s for unknown conversation_id.\n8. Update existing /start and /message tests if they assert non-empty `phrase_suggestions` ŌĆö they should now expect empty arrays from the initial response.\n\nMeasure p50 latency before/after by timing /api/conversation/message in the integration test (logged via existing `logger.info`). Expected: ~30-45% reduction in /start and /message wall time since 1 of 2-3 sequential LLM calls is removed from the critical path.\n\nNo schema changes required.",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/routers/conversation.py", "frontend/src/api.ts", "frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx", "tests/integration/test_conversation_api.py"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
