{
  "type": "refactor",
  "title": "Parallelize opening message and role-briefing LLM calls in /conversation/start",
  "description": "In app/routers/conversation.py start_conversation(), when role_swap=True the endpoint makes two sequential Copilot calls: first the opening greeting (line 352 safe_llm_call ŌåÆ copilot.ask), then the role-briefing phrases (line 386 _get_briefing ŌåÆ copilot.ask). Each call is ~1-3s, so role-swap starts pay double latency for a sequence that has no data dependency between the calls. Refactor to issue both calls concurrently via asyncio.gather when req.role_swap and user_role_name are set, while keeping the non-role-swap path unchanged. Implementation details:\n\n1. Define _get_briefing() as today but execute it concurrently with the opening call: when role_swap, run `opening, role_briefing = await asyncio.gather(safe_llm_call(opening_lambda, context='start_conversation'), _get_briefing())`. Wrap in try/except so that if opening fails we still call conv_dal.delete_conversation(db, conversation_id) and re-raise ŌĆö but role_briefing failure must remain non-fatal (return [] inside _get_briefing as it already does). Use return_exceptions=True or a small helper to ensure briefing errors do not abort the gather.\n2. Keep the existing serial path when role_swap is False (no behavior change there).\n3. Add an INFO log mirroring the message-endpoint style: `logger.info('Parallel start LLM calls completed (%.1fs)', time.monotonic()-t0)` so we can verify the speedup in logs.\n\nTesting:\n- Update/extend tests/integration/test_conversation_api.py (or wherever start is tested) to assert role_swap=True still returns user_role and role_briefing populated, and that a forced briefing failure still returns 200 with role_briefing=[].\n- Add a unit-style test that mocks copilot.ask to record call timings/order and asserts both calls were dispatched before either awaited (e.g., using a single AsyncMock with side_effect tracking call_count before the first sleep completes).\n\nThis complements iter 624 (lazy helpers on /message) by also shaving a round-trip off /start specifically for role-swap scenarios, addressing PERF-HIGH backlog item (2) ŌĆśstart Ńü¦2Õø×Õæ╝ŃüČ Copilot Õæ╝Õć║ŃüŚŃéÆ1Õø×ńĄ▒ÕÉłŌĆÖ in its parallelization variant (safer than merging into a single prompt because the briefing schema differs from a free-form greeting).",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/routers/conversation.py", "tests/integration/test_conversation_api.py"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "small"
}
