```json
{
  "type": "perf",
  "title": "Bound /message LLM context: truncate conversation history to last N turns",
  "description": "Currently `app/dal/conversation.py::format_history_text` returns the ENTIRE conversation as a single string and `app/routers/conversation.py::send_message` injects all of it into the conversation LLM prompt on every turn. As sessions grow (10-30+ messages), this linearly inflates input tokens for the latency-critical /message endpoint, slowing each round-trip and increasing cost. /start (624), /start parallelization (625), /end parallelization (626), and lazy helpers were prior wins; remaining angle from the backlog is prompt/token reduction. This change targets that directly with a small, measurable, easily-testable diff.\n\nChanges:\n1. `app/dal/conversation.py`: extend `format_history_text(db, conversation_id, max_turns: int | None = None)` with an optional `max_turns` parameter. When set, query only the most recent `max_turns` rows using `ORDER BY created_at DESC, id DESC LIMIT ?`, then reverse them to chronological order before joining. When `max_turns is None`, behavior is identical to today (no breaking change for /end summary which needs full history). If the original message count exceeded `max_turns`, prepend a single short marker line `\"[earlier turns omitted for brevity]\"` so the model knows context was truncated.\n2. `app/routers/conversation.py::send_message`: call `format_history_text(db, req.conversation_id, max_turns=16)` (8 user + 8 assistant turns Ōēł enough for coherent continuation). Leave `/end` (`format_history_text(...)` without max_turns) untouched so summaries remain faithful.\n3. Keep the constant local in conversation.py (e.g. `MESSAGE_HISTORY_MAX_TURNS = 16`) so it is easy to tune later without config.yaml churn.\n\nNo schema changes. No frontend changes. No new endpoints. The grammar-check LLM call (which only uses the user's single message) is unaffected.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- `format_history_text(db, cid)` (no kwarg) returns full history exactly as before ŌĆö existing tests pass unchanged.\n- `format_history_text(db, cid, max_turns=4)` on a conversation with 10 messages returns a string containing the marker `[earlier turns omitted for brevity]` followed by exactly the last 4 messages in chronological order.\n- `format_history_text(db, cid, max_turns=100)` on a 3-message conversation returns the full history with NO marker (truncation only when actually needed).\n- `/message` integration test still passes (mocked copilot) and the prompt passed to `copilot.ask` for a long-history conversation contains the marker string and does NOT contain the earliest message content.\n- `/end` summary path continues to receive the full history (verify via existing tests; no regression).\n\nTests to add (`tests/unit/test_conversation_dal.py`):\n- `test_format_history_text_no_truncation_default`\n- `test_format_history_text_max_turns_truncates_with_marker`\n- `test_format_history_text_max_turns_larger_than_history_no_marker`\n- `test_format_history_text_preserves_chronological_order_after_truncation`\n\nAnd one router test (`tests/integration/test_conversation_router.py` or similar existing file): assert /message prompt for a >16-message conversation includes the omitted-marker and excludes the first message content.",
  "files_to_modify": [
    "app/dal/conversation.py",
    "app/routers/conversation.py",
    "tests/unit/test_conversation_dal.py",
    "tests/integration/test_conversation_router.py"
  ],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "small"
}
