{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Per-message slow-replay (­¤Éó 0.6├Ś) button on assistant turns in Conversation",
  "description": "Add a 'Slow Replay' button next to the existing ­¤öŖ speak button on every assistant message in the Conversation page so learners can re-listen to native-paced replies at a slower rate (0.6├Ś) without changing their global TTS speed setting. This supports listening-skill drilling and matches the app's listening/speaking focus.\n\nChanges:\n\n1. `frontend/src/hooks/useSpeechSynthesis.ts`: Extend `speak` signature to `speak(text: string, lang?: string, rateOverride?: number)`. When `rateOverride` is provided (e.g. 0.6), use it for `utterance.rate` instead of `rateRef.current`. The global `rate` state and existing single-arg/two-arg call sites continue to work unchanged (backward compatible). Update the `UseSpeechSynthesisReturn` type accordingly.\n\n2. `frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx`: In the assistant-message render block (where the existing Volume2 / ­¤öŖ replay button lives), add a sibling button using the existing `Headphones` icon (already imported) with aria-label 'Slow replay (0.6├Ś)'. On click, call `speak(message.content, 'en-US', 0.6)`. Style consistently with the existing replay button (same hover/focus states, dark mode classes).\n\n3. `frontend/src/__tests__/useSpeechSynthesis.test.ts` (new or extend existing): Add a unit test that mocks `window.speechSynthesis` and `SpeechSynthesisUtterance`, calls `speak('hello', 'en-US', 0.6)`, and asserts the created utterance has `rate === 0.6` while a subsequent `speak('hi')` call uses the default `rateRef.current` (0.9). Also assert backward compatibility: `speak('hi', 'en-US')` still works with no third arg.\n\nWhy: Listening at native speed is hard for learners; a one-click slow-replay per message is a low-friction repetitive listening drill mechanic that complements the existing ­¤öŖ button. It is purely client-side (no backend / no model calls), avoids overlap with recent perf work, and is small + testable.",
  "files_to_modify": [
