```json
{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Track Copilot call latency (p50/p95) and expose via metrics endpoint",
  "description": "The PERF-HIGH backlog item asks for 'p50 Õ┐£ńŁöµÖéķ¢ōŃéÆĶ©łµĖ¼ŃüŚŃü”ŃāŁŃé░Ńü½Ķ©śķī▓' so future conversation-latency optimizations can be measured. Currently `app/copilot_client.py` logs per-call session/llm/total durations as one-off lines, but there is no aggregation, making it impossible to see whether iters 624-628 actually moved p50/p95.\n\nChanges:\n\n1. **`app/copilot_client.py`** ŌĆö Add a module-level `LatencyTracker` class with thread-safe (asyncio.Lock-free, just per-event-loop) `record(label: str, session_s: float, llm_s: float, total_s: float)` and `snapshot() -> dict` methods. `snapshot()` returns, for each label and 'all', `{count, p50_s, p95_s, p99_s, mean_s, max_s, last_s}` for both `llm` and `total` durations. Keep a bounded ring buffer (e.g. last 200 samples per label) to cap memory. Expose a module function `get_latency_tracker()` returning the singleton.\n\n   Modify `CopilotService.ask()` to accept an optional `label: str = 'default'` parameter and, after the existing log line, call `get_latency_tracker().record(label, session_s, llm_s, total_s)`. Also add a periodic aggregate log: when a label's count crosses each multiple of 20, emit `logger.info('Copilot latency [%s] n=%d p50=%.2fs p95=%.2fs total p50=%.2fs p95=%.2fs', ...)`.\n\n   Update `ask_json()` to forward the `label` kwarg.\n\n2. **`app/routers/conversation.py`** (and lightly the other routers that call `service.ask`/`ask_json` for conversation) ŌĆö pass `label='conversation_start'`, `'conversation_message'`, `'conversation_end'` at the call sites in conversation.py only (other routers can be left as default to keep the diff small).\n\n3. **New `app/routers/metrics.py`** ŌĆö Tiny router with `GET /api/internal/copilot-metrics` returning `get_latency_tracker().snapshot()` as JSON. Register it in `app/main.py` (one-line include_router).\n\n4. **`tests/unit/test_copilot_latency.py`** ŌĆö New unit tests for `LatencyTracker`: empty snapshot, single record, percentile correctness on a known sample (e.g. records 1..100 ŌåÆ p50Ōēł50, p95Ōēł95), ring-buffer cap (record 300, count stays at 200), per-label isolation.\n\n5. **`tests/integration/test_metrics_endpoint.py`** ŌĆö Integration test that hits `/api/internal/copilot-metrics`, verifies 200 + expected schema (dict keyed by label with `count`, `llm`, `total` sub-dicts), and that after manually calling `tracker.record()` the snapshot reflects it.\n\nNo schema changes. No config.yaml changes. The tracker is in-memory only (acceptable: this is a single-process dev/learning app, and the backlog only asks for logs + visibility). This unblocks measuring the next round of perf work (prompt shortening, streaming).",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/copilot_client.py", "app/routers/conversation.py", "app/routers/metrics.py", "tests/unit/test_copilot_latency.py", "tests/integration/test_metrics_endpoint.py"],
